# Carbon Design System Integration

## Overview

This project uses IBM's **Carbon Design System** as the primary UI component library. Carbon is imported from `@carbon/react` v1.83.0-rc.0.

## Installation and Setup

Carbon is already installed and configured:

{
  "dependencies": {
    "@carbon/react": "^1.83.0-rc.0"
  }
}


Global Carbon styles are imported in `src/index.scss`.

## Available Components

Carbon provides a comprehensive set of components. Refer to `design-system-docs/AGENTS.md` for a complete list and `design-system-docs/*.mdx` files for detailed component documentation.

### Commonly Used Components

**Layout & Structure:**
- `Grid`, `Column`, `Row` - Responsive grid system
- `Stack` - Vertical/horizontal layout with spacing
- `Theme` - Theme context provider

**UI Shell (Navigation):**
- `Header`, `HeaderName`, `HeaderNavigation`
- `HeaderMenuItem`, `HeaderGlobalBar`, `HeaderGlobalAction`
- `SideNav`, `SideNavItems`, `SideNavLink`, `SideNavMenu`

**Forms & Inputs:**
- `TextInput`, `TextArea`, `PasswordInput`
- `Dropdown`, `Select`, `ComboBox`, `MultiSelect`
- `Checkbox`, `RadioButton`, `Toggle`
- `NumberInput`, `DatePicker`, `TimePicker`
- `Button`, `IconButton`

**Data Display:**
- `DataTable` (with Table*, TableRow, TableCell components)
- `StructuredList`
- `Tile`, `ClickableTile`, `ExpandableTile`

**Feedback & Status:**
- `InlineNotification`, `ToastNotification`, `ActionableNotification`
- `Loading`, `InlineLoading`, `SkeletonText`, `SkeletonPlaceholder`
- `ProgressBar` ✅ (OK to use)
- ❌ `ProgressIndicator` **BANNED** - Use `StepBreadcrumb` instead (see `.builder/rules/banned-components.mdc`)

## ⛔ Never Replace Carbon Components With Custom HTML

When a design shows any of the UI patterns below, **always use the Carbon component**. Never build a custom `<div>`/`<button>` equivalent — doing so breaks theme support and accessibility.

| Design shows… | Use Carbon component |
|---|---|
| Yellow/red/blue/green alert or banner | `<InlineNotification lowContrast kind="warning|error|info|success">` |
| Auto-dismiss toast message | `<ToastNotification>` |
| Dismiss-able notification | `<InlineNotification onCloseButtonClick={…}>` |
| Loading spinner | `<Loading>` or `<InlineLoading>` |
| Status tag / chip / badge | `<Tag>` |
| Accordion / expandable row | `<Accordion>` |
| Confirm / alert dialog | `<Modal>` |
| Tooltip on hover | `<Tooltip>` |
| Pagination bar | `<Pagination>` |
| Progress bar (linear) | `<ProgressBar>` |

### InlineNotification — the most commonly misused pattern

Whenever a design shows a coloured alert banner with an icon and optional dismiss button, reach for `InlineNotification`. **Always add `lowContrast` on light-mode pages** or it will render with a dark background.


// ✅ Correct
import { InlineNotification } from '@carbon/react';

{visible && (
  <InlineNotification
    kind="warning"       // error | warning | info | success
    lowContrast          // REQUIRED on white/light pages
    title="Warning:"
    subtitle="Something needs your attention."
    onCloseButtonClick={() => setVisible(false)}
    aria-label="Dismiss warning notification"
    statusIconDescription="warning"
  />
)}


Full guidance: `.builder/rules/inline-notification-usage.mdc`

**Navigation & Controls:**
