### DataTable with Pagination — Correct Pattern

This is the definitive pattern. Read all the rules below before implementing any table.

#### ⛔ Three rules that must always be followed

**Rule 1 — Never put `title` or `description` on `TableContainer`.**
Those props make Carbon render an internal header div with its own `$layer-01` background. On a page whose wrapper uses `var(--background-primary)`, those two surfaces resolve to different values in dark mode (`#262626` vs `#161616`), producing a floating band of wrong colour at the top of the table. Put your title and description in your own markup above the `DataTable` instead.

**Rule 2 — Never wrap `DataTable` in `<Layer>`.**
`Layer` remaps `$layer` tokens but leaves `$background` alone. This causes different internal sections of `TableContainer` and `Pagination` to resolve different token levels, producing a striped / mismatched footer. Do not use `Layer` as a workaround.

**Rule 3 — Always add the Pagination SCSS override (see below).**
Carbon's `Pagination` component uses `$background` for its left panel and `$layer` for other sections. In dark mode these are different values, creating a split-colour footer. The SCSS override below fixes this in a theme-safe way using Carbon's own `--cds-` custom properties.

#### ✅ Correct JSX

```jsx
import {
  DataTable,
  TableContainer,
  Table,
  TableHead,
  TableRow,
  TableHeader,
  TableBody,
  TableCell,
  Pagination,
  Tag,
} from '@carbon/react';

// ─── Your own header — title and description go HERE, not in TableContainer ───
<div className="my-table-header">
  <div>
    <h2>My Items</h2>
    <p>Showing all active records</p>
  </div>
  <Button kind="primary" renderIcon={Add}>Add Item</Button>
</div>

// ─── DataTable — no title/description on TableContainer ───────────────────────
<DataTable rows={rows} headers={headers} isSortable>
  {({ rows, headers, getHeaderProps, getRowProps, getTableProps, getTableContainerProps }) => (
    <TableContainer {...getTableContainerProps()}>
      <Table {...getTableProps()} size="md">
        <TableHead>
          <TableRow>
            {headers.map((header) => (
              <TableHeader key={header.key} {...getHeaderProps({ header })}>
                {header.header}
              </TableHeader>
            ))}
          </TableRow>
        </TableHead>
        <TableBody>
          {rows.map((row) => (
            <TableRow key={row.id} {...getRowProps({ row })}>
              {row.cells.map((cell) => (
                <TableCell key={cell.id}>
                  {cell.info.header === 'status' ? (
                    // ✅ Use <Tag> for status — never custom badge spans with hardcoded colours
                    <Tag type={cell.value === 'Active' ? 'green' : 'red'} size="sm">
                      {cell.value}
                    </Tag>
                  ) : (
                    cell.value
                  )}
                </TableCell>
              ))}
            </TableRow>
          ))}
        </TableBody>
      </Table>
      <Pagination
        totalItems={totalItems}
        pageSize={pageSize}
        pageSizes={[5, 10, 25, 100]}
        page={page}
        onChange={({ page: p, pageSize: ps }) => { setPage(p); setPageSize(ps); }}
      />
    </TableContainer>
  )}
</DataTable>
```

#### ✅ Required SCSS — add this for EVERY page that renders a Pagination

Carbon's `Pagination` uses different internal tokens for different sections (`$background` for the left panel, `$layer` for the rest). This override normalises the entire component to `--cds-layer-01` using Carbon's own CSS custom properties, so it stays correct in both light and dark themes without hardcoding any colour.

Scope it under your page class so it does not affect other pages:

```scss
// ─── Pagination contrast fix ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
// Carbon's Pagination uses $background for its left panel and $layer for other
// sections. In dark mode these resolve to different values, producing a
// split-colour footer. --cds-layer-01 is Carbon's own theme-aware custom
// property, so this works in both light and dark without hardcoded colours.

.my-page-wrapper .cds--pagination {
  background-color: var(--cds-layer-01);
  border-top-color: var(--cds-border-subtle-01);

  .cds--pagination__left,
  .cds--pagination__right {
    background-color: var(--cds-layer-01);
  }

  .cds--select-input {
    background-color: var(--cds-layer-01);
    &:hover { background-color: var(--cds-layer-hover-01); }
  }

  .cds--pagination__button {
    background-color: var(--cds-layer-01);
    &:hover:not(:disabled) { background-color: var(--cds-layer-hover-01); }
  }
}
```

#### ❌ Common mistakes

```jsx
// ❌ WRONG — title/description cause a layer-mismatch header in dark mode
<TableContainer
  title="My Table"
  description="5 items found"
  {...getTableContainerProps()}
>

// ❌ WRONG — Layer remaps $layer but not $background, causing striped footer
<Layer>
  <DataTable ...>

// ❌ WRONG — hardcoded badge colours break in dark mode
<span style={{ background: '#defbe6', color: '#198038' }}>Active</span>

// ✅ CORRECT — Carbon Tag uses theme tokens automatically
<Tag type="green" size="sm">Active</Tag>
```

